{"title_page": "\u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel", "text_new": "{{short description|Turkish modern pentathlete}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name             = \u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel\n| birth_name       =\n| image            =\n| image_size       =\n| caption          =\n| nationality      = Turkey\n| residence        =\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1997|02|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place      =\n| height           = {{height|m=1.67}}\n| weight           = {{cvt|53|kg}}\n| country          = {{TUR}}\n| sport            = [[Modern Pentathlon]]\n| event            =\n| turnedpro        =\n| coach            =\n| worlds           =\n| regionals        =\n| nationals        =\n| olympics         =\n| highestranking   =\n| pb               =\n| medaltemplates   =\n{{MedalCountry|{{TUR}} }}\n{{MedalSport|[[Modern Pentathlon]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[European Modern Pentathlon Championships|European Championships]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 European Modern Pentathlon Championships|2017 Minsk]] |Individual}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2016 European Modern Pentathlon Championships|2016 Sofia]] |Individual}}\n{{MedalCompetition|European Junior Championships }}\n{{MedalGold|[[2018 in modern pentathlon#Contintental modern pentathlon championships|2018 El Prat de Llobregat]]|Individual }}\n{{MedalCompetition|UIPM Youth \"A\" World Championships }}\n{{MedalGold|2015 Buenos Aires|Individual }}\n{{MedalCompetition|European Youth \"B\" Championships}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2013 in modern pentathlon#Continental modern pentathlon championships|2013 Minsk]] |Individual}}\n| updated          =\n}}\n\n'''\u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel''' (born 26 February 1997) is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] female [[Modern pentathlon|modern pentathlete]].<ref name=\"aa\"/>\n\n==Private life==\n\u00d6zy\u00fcksel was born to a retired worker father and a school counselor mother, who had lost her sight at the age of 15 due to [[ocular hypertension]]. She became very sick two weeks after her birth on 26 February 1997. In the beginning, it was thought that she had cancer. However, a Turkish physician working in the United States, who was in Turkey for a three-day conference, diagnosed her with [[Infantile hemangioma]], which can be fatal if not treated. She underwent a laser therapy, and could get her health again.<ref name=\"h1\"/>\n\n==Sports career==\nAt the age of only nine, \u00d6zy\u00fcksel became champion at the World Championships for Cadets. In 2014, she decided to quit pentathlon upon suggestions of her coach. However, the Federation insisted in her career, and sent her for training to Hungary, where she stayed eleven months. After she broke a world record there, she became unwelcome by the Hungarian coach, and had to return home ahead of schedule. After her return, the Federation set up a 10-member team including a [[psychologist]], a [[dietitian]], a [[masseur]] and a physician, to prepare her for the Olympics. She trained eight hours a day for four and half months.<ref name=\"h1\"/>\n\nShe won the gold medal at the [[Union Internationale de Pentathlon Moderne|UIPM]] 2015 Youth \"A\" World Championships held in [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina.<ref name=\"hdn1\"/> At the same competition, she set two world records for youth, in overall with 1,065 points and in combined with a time of 11:55.00 and 585 points.<ref name=\"uipm1\"/> She earned a quota spot at the [[Turkey at the 2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil. She is the first ever Olympic modern pentathlon participant from Turkey.<ref name=\"f1\"/> At the [[2017 European Modern Pentathlon Championships|2017 European Championships]] in [[Minsk]], Belarus, she took the bronze medal.<ref name=\"m1\"/> In the Stage 4 of [[2017 Modern Penthatlon World Cup|2017 World Cup]] held in [[Drzonk\u00f3w]], Poland, she won the bronze medal, and set a world record for juniors in combined with a time of 11:57.53 and 583 points.<ref name=\"uipm1\"/><ref name=\"h2\"/> \u00d6zy\u00fcksel captured the gold medal at the 2018 Modern Pentathlon Junior European Championships held in [[El Prat de Llobregat]], Spain. She broke the world record with a total of 1,376 points competing in the [[Union Internationale de Pentathlon Moderne#The five events|five events]] of fencing, swimming, riding and shootin events.<ref name=\"ht1\"/> She set world records in the running and the shooting events at the [[2019 European Modern Pentathlon Championships]] held in [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], United Kingdom.<ref name=\"ntvs1\"/>\n\nIn 2019, she received the \"Mustafa V. Ko\u00e7 Sports Award\" worth of {{Turkish lira}} 250,000 (approx. USD 47,000). The prize was established jointly by the [[Ko\u00e7 Holding]] and the [[Turkish Olympic Committee]] in commemoration of the late [[Mustafa Vehbi Ko\u00e7]] (1960\u20132016).<ref name=\"aa1\"/>\n\n==Recods==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n|+World Records<ref name=\"uipm1\"/>\n|-\n!Event !!Record !!Competition !!Location ||Date\n|-\n|Overall ||1,065 points ||rowspan=2 |UIPM Youth \"A\" World Championships Final ||rowspan=2 |{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Buenos Aires]] ||rowspan=2 align=right |31 August 2015\n|-\n|Combined ||11:55.00<br>585 points\n|-\n|Combined ||11:57.53<br>583 points ||[[2017 Modern Penthatlon World Cup|2017 World Cup]] Stage 4 Final ||{{flagicon|POL}} [[Drzonk\u00f3w]] ||align=right |28 May 2017 \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"aa\">{{cite web |url=http://www.all-athletics.com/node/693076 |publisher=All Athletics |title=Ilke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel |accessdate=2016-06-23 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"f1\">{{cite news |url=http://www.fanatik.com.tr/2016/06/16/modern-pentatlonda-bir-ilke-1238629 |newspaper=[[Fanatik]] |title=Modern pentatlonda bir \u2018\u0130lke\u2019 |date=2016-06-17 |language=Turkish |accessdate=2016-06-23 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"hdn1\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkish-athlete-crowned-modern-pentathlon-world-champion-marking-first.aspx?pageID=449&nID=88026&NewsCatID=371 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet Daily News]] |title=Turkish athlete crowned modern pentathlon world champion, marking first |date=2015-09-05 |accessdate=2016-06-23 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"h1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/once-olumu-asti-sonra-tarih-yazdi-40132413 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |title=\u00d6nce \u00f6l\u00fcm\u00fc a\u015ft\u0131, sonra tarih yazd\u0131 |date=5 July 2016 |language=tr |accessdate=5 September 2018 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"h2\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/ilke-ozyuksel-dunya-rekoru-kirarak-bronz-madal-40472115 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |title=\u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel, d\u00fcnya rekoru k\u0131rarak bronz madalya kazand\u0131 |author=Ata, Ercan |date=27 May 2017 |language=tr |accessdate=28 September 2019 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ht1\">{{cite news |url=https://www.haberturk.com/ankara-haberleri/15741541-bakan-bak-ilke-ozyukseli-kutladi |newspaper=[[Habert\u00fcrk]] |title=Bakan Bak, \u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel'i kutlad\u0131 |date=21 June 2018 |language=tr |accessdate=5 September 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"uipm1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.uipmworld.org/world-records-0 |publisher=UIPM World Penthatlon |title=World Records |accessdate=28 September 2019 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"ntvs1\">{{cite news |url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/spor/ilke-ozyukselden-dunya-rekoru,p26N4ZqY80yEOkLWKBn4Bg |newspaper=[[NTV Spor]] |title=\u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel'den d\u00fcnya rekoru |date=13 August 2019 |language=tr |accessdate=28 September 2019 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"aa1\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/sirkethaberleri/holding/ilke-ozyuksel-mustafa-v-koc-spor-odulunun-sahibi-oldu-/653360 |newspaper=[[Anadolu News Agency]] |title=\u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel, \"Mustafa V. Ko\u00e7 Spor \u00d6d\u00fcl\u00fc\"n\u00fcn sahibi oldu  |date=25 September 2019 |language=tr |accessdate=28 September 2019 }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"m1\">{{cite news |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/ilke-ozyukselden-bronz-madalya-2489342 |newspaper=[[Milliyet]] |title=\u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel'den bronz madalya! |date=22 July 2017 |language=tr |accessdate=28 September 2019 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{UIPM}} <!--uses Wikidata-->\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ozyuksel, Ilke}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Turkish female modern pentathletes]]\n[[Category:Modern pentathletes at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics]]\n[[Category:Modern pentathletes at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic modern pentathletes of Turkey]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Turkish modern pentathlete}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name             = \u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel\n| birth_name       =\n| image            =\n| image_size       =\n| caption          =\n| nationality      = Turkey\n| residence        =\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1997|02|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place      =\n| height           = {{height|m=1.67}}\n| weight           = {{cvt|53|kg}}\n| country          = {{TUR}}\n| sport            = [[Modern Pentathlon]]\n| event            =\n| turnedpro        =\n| coach            =\n| worlds           =\n| regionals        =\n| nationals        =\n| olympics         =\n| highestranking   =\n| pb               =\n| medaltemplates   =\n{{MedalCountry|{{TUR}} }}\n{{MedalSport|[[Modern Pentathlon]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[European Modern Pentathlon Championships|European Championships]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 European Modern Pentathlon Championships|2017 Minsk]] |Individual}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2016 European Modern Pentathlon Championships|2016 Sofia]] |Individual}}\n{{MedalCompetition|European Junior Championships }}\n{{MedalGold|[[2018 in modern pentathlon#Contintental modern pentathlon championships|2018 El Prat de Llobregat]]|Individual }}\n{{MedalCompetition|UIPM Youth \"A\" World Championships }}\n{{MedalGold|2015 Buenos Aires|Individual }}\n{{MedalCompetition|European Youth \"B\" Championships}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2013 in modern pentathlon#Continental modern pentathlon championships|2013 Minsk]] |Individual}}\n| updated          =\n}}\n\n'''\u0130lke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel''' (born 26 February 1997) is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] female [[Modern pentathlon|modern pentathlete]].<ref name=\"aa\"/>\n\n==Private life==\n\u00d6zy\u00fcksel was born to a retired worker father and a school counselor mother, who had lost her sight at the age of 15 due to [[ocular hypertension]]. She became very sick two weeks after her birth on 26 February 1997. In the beginning, it was thought that she had cancer. However, a Turkish physician working in the United States, who was in Turkey for a three-day conference, diagnosed her with [[Infantile hemangioma]], which can be fatal if not treated. She underwent a laser therapy, and could get her heath again.<ref name=\"h1\"/>\n\n==Sports career==\nAt the age of only nine, \u00d6zy\u00fcksel became champion at the World Championships for Cadets. In 2014, she decided to quit pentathlon upon suggestions of her coach. However, the Federation insisted in her career, and sent her for training to Hungary, where she stayed eleven months. After she broke a world record there, she became unwelcome by the Hungarian coach, and had to return home ahead of schedule. After her return, the Federation set up a 10-member team including a [[psychologist]], a [[dietitian]], a [[masseur]] and a physician, to prepare her for the Olympics. She trained eight hours a day for four and half months.<ref name=\"h1\"/>\n\nShe won the gold medal at the [[Union Internationale de Pentathlon Moderne|UIPM]] 2015 Youth \"A\" World Championships held in [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina.<ref name=\"hdn1\"/> At the same competition, she set two world records for youth, in overall with 1,065 points and in combined with a time of 11:55.00 and 585 points.<ref name=\"uipm1\"/> She earned a quota spot at the [[Turkey at the 2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil. She is the first ever Olympic modern pentathlon participant from Turkey.<ref name=\"f1\"/> At the [[2017 European Modern Pentathlon Championships|2017 European Championships]] in [[Minsk]], Belarus, she took the bronze medal.<ref name=\"m1\"/> In the Stage 4 of [[2017 Modern Penthatlon World Cup|2017 World Cup]] held in [[Drzonk\u00f3w]], Poland, she won the bronze medal, and set a world record for juniors in combined with a time of 11:57.53 and 583 points.<ref name=\"uipm1\"/><ref name=\"h2\"/> \u00d6zy\u00fcksel captured the gold medal at the 2018 Modern Pentathlon Junior European Championships held in [[El Prat de Llobregat]], Spain. She broke the world record with a total of 1,376 points competing in the [[Union Internationale de Pentathlon Moderne#The five events|five events]] of fencing, swimming, riding and shootin events.<ref name=\"ht1\"/> She set world records in the running and the shooting events at the [[2019 European Modern Pentathlon Championships]] held in [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], United Kingdom.<ref name=\"ntvs1\"/>\n\nIn 2019, she received the \"Mustafa V. Ko\u00e7 Sports Award\" worth of {{Turkish lira}} 250,000 (approx. USD 47,000). The prize was established jointly by the [[Ko\u00e7 Holding]] and the [[Turkish Olympic Committee]] in commemoration of the late [[Mustafa Vehbi Ko\u00e7]] (1960\u20132016).<ref name=\"aa1\"/>\n\n==Recods==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n|+World Records<ref name=\"uipm1\"/>\n|-\n!Event !!Record !!Competition !!Location ||Date\n|-\n|Overall ||1,065 points ||rowspan=2 |UIPM Youth \"A\" World Championships Final ||rowspan=2 |{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Buenos Aires]] ||rowspan=2 align=right |31 August 2015\n|-\n|Combined ||11:55.00<br>585 points\n|-\n|Combined ||11:57.53<br>583 points ||[[2017 Modern Penthatlon World Cup|2017 World Cup]] Stage 4 Final ||{{flagicon|POL}} [[Drzonk\u00f3w]] ||align=right |28 May 2017 \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"aa\">{{cite web |url=http://www.all-athletics.com/node/693076 |publisher=All Athletics |title=Ilke \u00d6zy\u00fcksel |accessdate=2016-06-23 }}